  "prompt": "What's Home Depot's return/exchange policy?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Home Depot generally has a return/exchange policy that allows customers to return most new, unused items within 90 days of purchase for a full refund or exchange. Here are some details:\n\n1. **Receipt**: It's best to have your receipt, as it makes the return process easier. If you don't have a receipt, Home Depot may still process the return using your purchase history if you used a credit card or a Home Depot account.\n\n2. **Extended Return Periods**: Certain items, such as seasonal merchandise, may have different return periods. For example, major appliances typically have a 30-day return period.\n\n3. **Condition of Items**: Items should ideally be unused and in their original packaging. Opened or partially used items may be subject to restocking fees or may not be eligible for return.\n\n4. **Prohibited Items**: Some items, such as gift cards, plants, and custom products (like special order doors or windows), may not be returnable.\n\n5. **Commercial Accounts**: Businesses may have a different return policy, often impacted by their specific agreements with Home Depot.\n\nPolicies may vary by store location and can change, so it's recommended to check Home Depot's official website or contact your local store for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
